item.title: Our Planet is Constantly Spinning
item.dc:creator: millajaaskelainen
item.content:encoded: The Sun is not the only object that may appear less blue in the atmosphere. Distant clouds or snowy mountaintops may appear yellowish. The effect is not very obvious on clear days, but is very pronounced when clouds cover the line of sight, reducing the blue hue from scattered sunlight.
